In the first test case you can use the following sequence of operations:
•  add $1$;
•  add $2 \cdot 10^0 = 2$;
•  add $2 \cdot 10^0 = 2$;
•  add $2 \cdot 10^0 = 2$.  $1 + 2 + 2 + 2 = 7$.
In the second test case you can use the following sequence of operations:
•  add $3 \cdot 10^1 = 30$;
•  add $3 \cdot 10^0 = 3$;
•  add $3 \cdot 10^0 = 3$;
•  add $3 \cdot 10^0 = 3$;
•  add $3 \cdot 10^0 = 3$.  $30 + 3 + 3 + 3 + 3 = 42$.
